      • factory

        public static Props.Factory factory()

      • bind

        public <T,​R extends Prop<T>> R bind​(R prop,
                                          @Nullable
                                          java.lang.String resolverId)
        Binds the specified prop to the current Props registry.

        If a non-null resolverId is specified, it will link the prop to that resolver.

        Throws:
        BindException - if attempting to bind a Prop for a key which was already bound to another object. This is to encourage efficiency and define a single object per key, keeping memory usage low(er). Use the retrieveProp(String) and retrieve(String) methods to get a pre-existing instance.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the specified resolverId is not known to the registry.

      • resolvePropLayers

        public <T> java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​T> resolvePropLayers​(Prop<T> prop)
        Returns a LinkedHashMap containing mappings for each resolver which contained a value for the specified Prop's key.

        The map can be iterated over in and will return Resolvers order by priority, lowest-to-highest.
